            <h2 id="introduction"><span class="section-number">2</span>Introduction</h2>
            <p>Neon Innovation Lab ("we," "our," or "us") operates the API Verse mobile application (the "Service"). This Privacy Policy informs you of our policies regarding the collection, use, and disclosure of personal data when you use our Service.</p>

            <p>API Verse is designed to help users discover, explore, and test public APIs on the go. We are committed to protecting your privacy and being transparent about our data practices.</p>

            <h2 id="information-collect"><span class="section-number">3</span>Information We Collect</h2>

            <h3>3.1 Data Collected Automatically</h3>
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>üéØ Advertising Data</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>We use Google AdMob to display advertisements in our app</li>
                    <li>AdMob may collect device information, advertising identifiers, and usage data for ad personalization</li>
                    <li>This includes but is not limited to: device type, operating system, IP address, and app usage patterns</li>
                    <li><strong>AdMob Publisher ID:</strong> ca-app-pub-5443624300995840</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>‚öôÔ∏è Technical Data</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Device information (model, operating system version)</li>
                    <li>App performance data</li>
                    <li>Crash reports and error logs (when they occur)</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h3>3.2 Data You Provide</h3>
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>‚≠ê Favorites and Preferences</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>API favorites you save within the app</li>
                    <li>Theme preferences (light/dark mode)</li>
                    <li>This data is stored locally on your device using Hive database</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>üß™ API Testing Data</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>When you test APIs through our app, we temporarily process the requests</li>
                    <li>We do not store or log your API test requests or responses</li>
                    <li>All API testing is performed in real-time and not retained</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h3>3.3 Data We Do NOT Collect</h3>
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>üö´ What We Don't Collect</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Personal identification information (name, email, phone number)</li>
                    <li>Location data</li>
                    <li>Photos, contacts, or other sensitive device data</li>
                    <li>User accounts or login credentials (our app does not require registration)</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h2 id="how-we-use"><span class="section-number">4</span>How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <p>We use the collected information for the following purposes:</p>
            <ol>
                <li><strong>App Functionality:</strong> To provide core features like API discovery, favorites, and testing capabilities</li>
                <li><strong>Advertising:</strong> To display relevant advertisements through Google AdMob</li>
                <li><strong>App Improvement:</strong> To analyze app performance and fix technical issues</li>
                <li><strong>User Experience:</strong> To remember your preferences and provide a personalized experience</li>
            </ol>

            <h2 id="data-storage"><span class="section-number">5</span>Data Storage and Retention</h2>

            <h3>Local Storage</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Your favorites and preferences are stored locally on your device</li>
                <li>This data persists until you delete the app or clear the app's cache/data</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Third-Party Storage</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Advertising data is handled by Google AdMob according to their privacy policies</li>
                <li>We do not maintain servers or databases that store your personal information</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Data Retention Period</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Local data:</strong> Retained until you delete the app or clear app data/cache</li>
                <li><strong>Advertising data:</strong> Managed by Google AdMob according to their retention policies</li>
            </ul>

            <h2 id="third-party"><span class="section-number">6</span>Third-Party Services</h2>
            <p>Our app integrates with the following third-party services:</p>

            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>üéØ Google AdMob</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> Displaying advertisements</li>
                    <li><strong>Data Collected:</strong> Device information, advertising ID, usage patterns</li>
                    <li><strong>Privacy Policy:</strong> <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank">https://policies.google.com/privacy</a></li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>üåê PublicAPI.dev</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> Providing API catalog data</li>
                    <li><strong>Data Shared:</strong> None (we only retrieve public API information)</li>
                    <li><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://publicapi.dev" target="_blank">https://publicapi.dev</a></li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>üîó Third-Party APIs (During Testing)</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>When you test APIs, your requests are sent directly to the respective API providers</li>
                    <li>We do not intercept, store, or monitor these communications</li>
                    <li>Each API provider has their own privacy policy and terms of service</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h2 id="your-rights"><span class="section-number">7</span>Your Rights and Choices</h2>

            <h3>Data Control</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>You can clear your favorites and preferences at any time through the app</li>
                <li>You can delete all app data by clearing the app's cache/data in Android settings</li>
                <li>You can uninstall the app to remove all locally stored data</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Advertising Choices</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>You can opt out of personalized ads through your Android device settings</li>
                <li>Go to Settings > Google > Ads > Opt out of Ads Personalization</li>
                <li>You can reset your advertising ID in the same location</li>
            </ul>

            <h2 id="children"><span class="section-number">8</span>Children's Privacy</h2>
            <p>Our app does not specifically target children under the age of 13, and we do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us, and we will take steps to remove such information.</p>

            <h2 id="security"><span class="section-number">9</span>Security</h2>
            <p>We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your data:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Local data encryption through Android's built-in security features</li>
                <li>Secure API communications using HTTPS</li>
                <li>Regular security updates and patches</li>
                <li>No central servers storing personal data</li>
            </ul>

            <h2 id="changes"><span class="section-number">10</span>Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
            <p>We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Updating the "Last Updated" date at the top of this Privacy Policy</li>
                <li>Posting the new Privacy Policy in the app and on our website</li>
                <li>If significant changes occur, we may provide additional notice through the app</li>
            </ol>

            <h2 id="contact"><span class="section-number">11</span>Contact Information</h2>
            <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us:</p>

